Name: Ed Sweeney
AboutMe:
I am a software developer specializing in .NET and C# although I am fluent in Java and other languages. I work for a web application company called Real Time Solutions (www.rtsolutions.com). I also own SweyPro (www.sweypro.com) and create mobile and desktop apps in my spare time. My featured app is called DriverDiary.

DriverDiary is a vehicle tracking app that allows you to track your fuel efficiency, maintenance, parts and other expenses as well as view detailed statistics and graphs. The Pro version adds the ability to SYNC your data with a remote server and multiple Android devices...a feature that no other vehicle tracking app on Android offers. Try out DriverDiary if you get a chance and let me know if you like it and any feedback you may have.
